cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper deals with privacy-preserving protocols for traffic-update mobile applications, which involves sensitive location and movement data of users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the aggregation of user reports and the creation of traffic statistics, which suggests the categories cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely options. The use of differential privacy techniques further supports the possibility of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a relevant category. Finally, the development of a prototype implementation and experiments on a real-world dataset suggest the category cs.CY (Computers and Society) as a possible option.
